@REM==============================================================================

@node "PreRelease" "Pre-Release Informations"

                            @{b}Pre-Release Informations
                           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

FAME is a brand new MailBox program which seems to be becoming very popular
and FAMEous as we can see on the very positive reactions we receive
daily.

We already have many bug-reports and suggestions and we believe we will
get lots more from the very first release on.

We work hard on fixing all reported bugs and suggestions as best we
can, but it's impossible to do all at the same time.

The same with the documents.
The documents are not complete at all... we have to enhance and enlarge
the documents as to tie up with the FAME executables.

You have bought FAME in an early stage and because of this not everything
written here is 100% correct but we are working on it.


@{u}@{b}Known not described parts in FAME.guide@{uu}@{ub}

 - Not everything is completely described.

 - Gadgets which are not used yet in the SystemEditor.

   This means that there are some gadgets available in the System-
   Editor where a change on the settings takes no effect.
   They are implemented since the gui was created and also the structures
   are available and will be written with such gadget datas, but @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"}
   and @{"Server" link "Server.guide/Main"} are not yet using everything.
   In a later SystemEditor.guide release we will mark all those gadgets,
   because people think that there is a bug, but it's still not
   implemented. Of course we work on it to implement all, one after
   another.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Contents" "FAME Amigaguide Document - FAME SystemEditor Contents"

                      @{b}FAME SYSTEMEDITOR DOCUMENT CONTENTS
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

 - The SystemEditor is needed to configure the whole FAME BBS.
 - The SystemEditor is a commodity for easy handling.
   If you start SystemEditor twice the last activ window appears to front.
 - The SystemEditor is full gadtools driven and easy usable via mouse and
   the keyboard too.
 - Use the SystemEditor every time you have something to change or add like
   a new conference or Node.

                           @{" SystemEditor Main Window " link "SysEdMainWindow"}
                           @{"  SystemEditor ToolTypes  " link "SysEdToolTypes"}
                           @{"  SystemEditor Arguments  " link "SysEdArgs"}
                           @{"       Miscellaneous      " link "Miscellaneous"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SysEdToolTypes" "SystemEditor ToolTypes"


                           @{b}SystemEditor ToolTypes
                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}


If you start the SystemEditor from Workbench it looks for the depending
icon, normally 'SystemEditor.info' it's file name icon from the
SystemEditor. You can also start the SystemEditor from CLI with
@{"arguments" link "SysEdArgs"}. All @{"arguments" link "SysEdArgs"} have the same name as the ToolTypes from the icon,
but there are more @{"arguments" link "SysEdArgs"} available than ToolTypes. On start from CLI
ToolTypes will also be read, but @{"arguments" link "SysEdArgs"} will have a higher priority than
the ToolTypes.


Following ToolTypes are available:


@{b}@{u}BBSLOCATION@{ub}@{uu}

The BBS location of your FAME root directory.

Example: BBSLOCATION=DH0:FAME/


@{b}@{u}PUBSCREEN@{ub}@{uu}

If a valid PublicScreen is given SystemEditor will open on this screen
else SystemEditor will open on the default PublicScreen.
If this also fails SystemEditor will open on the workbench screen.

Example: PUBSCREEN=FAME_Node1


@{b}@{u}FRONTMOST@{ub}@{uu}

If set the SystemEditor will open on the front most screen if it's a
PublicScreen else SystemEditor will open on the default PublicScreen.
If this also fails SystemEditor will open on the workbench screen.

Example: FRONTMOST (it's a switch)


@{b}@{u}NOCHECK@{ub}@{uu}

Disables the directory and file scan on starting the SystemEditor.

Example: NOCHECK (it's a switch)


This scan is used for the first installation of FAME and later for your own
security to check if all files and directories needed by FAME are available.

Normal usage is to set the NOCHECK ToolType if you don't want to have the
check each time you start the SystemEditor, but you should start the
SystemEditor from time to time with the CHECK option then from CLI to check
if everything is ok, especially if you update your FAME to a newer version.

The check for directories and files is very fast on fast hard disks so
i would recommend you to leave the NOCHECK ToolType disabled except if you have a
very slow hard disk!!

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SysEdArgs" "SystemEditor Arguments"


                           @{b}SystemEditor Arguments
                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}


If you start the SystemEditor directly from a CLI/Shell it has the following
argument template:

BBSLOCATION/K,NOCHECK/S,CHECK/S,RESETNODECOUNTER/S,RESETCONFCOUNTER/S,
CREATE/S,JUMP/N,WINCLOSEQUIT/S,LOADFILE/K,PUBSCREEN/K,FRONTMOST/S


@{b}@{u}BBSLOCATION/K@{ub}@{uu}

The BBS location of your FAME root directory.

Example: BBSLOCATION=DH0:FAME/


@{b}@{u}NOCHECK/S@{ub}@{uu}

Disables the directory and file scan on starting the SystemEditor.

Example: NOCHECK (it's a switch)


@{b}@{u}CHECK/S@{ub}@{uu}

Overrides the @{"NOCHECK ToolType" link "SysEdToolTypes"}. If you want the SystemEditor to check
as default, just disable the @{"NOCHECK ToolType" link "SysEdToolTypes"}.

Example: CHECK (it's a switch)


@{b}@{u}RESETNODECOUNTER/S@{ub}@{uu}

Resets the internal Number Of Nodes counter.
Since the Number Of Nodes gadget is no longer used, because the SystemEditor
is able to handle this itself, the SystemEditor has this argument if something
strange happens. For example if someone removes Nodes by hand and not with the
SystemEditor the real Number Of Nodes is no longer known by the SystemEditor.

With this argument you force the SystemEditor to re-build the Number of Nodes.

Example: RESETNODECOUNTER (it's a switch)


@{b}@{u}RESETCONFCOUNTER/S@{ub}@{uu}

Resets the internal Number Of Conferences counter.
The SystemEditor is able to handle the Number Of Conferences itself and
because of this the SystemEditor has this argument if something strange
happens. For example, if someone removes Conferences by hand and not with the
SystemEditor, the real Number Of Conferences is no longer known by the
SystemEditor.

With this argument you force the SystemEditor to re-build the Number of
Conferences.

Example: RESETCONFCOUNTER (it's a switch)


@{b}@{u}CREATE/S@{ub}@{uu}

With 'CREATE' the SystemEditor creates all non existing directories and
files, but no requester will appear asking if it should do this.

Needed by the FAME installer script for first installation of FAME.

Example: CREATE (it's a switch)


@{b}@{u}JUMP/N@{ub}@{uu}

/N is the number of a defined window where the SystemEditor will automaticly
jump into.
If you call the SystemEditor like this: 'SystemEditor JUMP=5', the SystemEditor
opens all windows needed to get into the 'Ser/Mod/Scr' window of Node 0
(SystemEditor -> Node Edit -> Ser/Mod/Scr).

Note: You can combine 'JUMP' with 'LOADFILE' to load a specific Node.

Defined window numbers: Main             0
                        SystemDatas      1
                        MoreSystemDatas  2
                        ServerSettings   3
                        NodeEdit         4
                        SerModScr        5
                        MoreNodeEdit     6  // For compatibility reason
                        MoreNodeEditI    6
                        Conferences      7
                        AccessSecure     8
                        Levels           9
                        MoreLevels       10
                        ConferenceAccess 11
                        Presets          12
                        Activities       13
                        Doors            14
                        rESERVED1        15
                        rESERVED2        16
                        InternalDoors    17
                        ComputerTypes    18
                        ModemTypes       19
                        Screens          20
                        FileCheckers     21
                        TextLanguage     22
                        ExtXferMods      23
                        FAMEModules      24
                        ExternModules    25
                        UserFileBase     26
                        Protocols        27
                        DoonError        28
                        DoorPortNames    29
                        uNuSED2          30
                        uNuSED3          31
                        About            32
                        MoreNodeEditII   33

Note: The defined window numbers are also defined in the include file
      'Include:FAME/FAMEDefine.h'.

Example: JUMP=5


@{b}@{u}WINCLOSEQUIT/S@{ub}@{uu}

If the argument 'WINCLOSEQUIT' is set, the SystemEditor will quit if
the last active window is closed.

Example: WINCLOSEQUIT (it's a switch)


@{b}@{u}LOADFILE/K@{ub}@{uu}

Load a data file into a specific window (open this window with JUMP/N).

Possibilities: Node Edit  : <Node number>.
               Conferences: <Conference number>.
               Levels     : <Level number>.
               ConfAccess : <Conf access data file>.
               Presets    : <Preset number (-1 = new user preset = default)>.
               Doors      : <Door data file + complete path>.
               Screens    : <Node number>.
               FileChecker: <Checker data file name (extension)>.

Example: LOADFILE=0 JUMP=5


@{b}@{u}PUBSCREEN/K@{ub}@{uu}

If a valid PublicScreen is given SystemEditor will open on this screen
else SystemEditor will open on the default PublicScreen.
If this also fails SystemEditor will open on the workbench screen.

Example: PUBSCREEN=FAME_Node1


@{b}@{u}FRONTMOST/S@{ub}@{uu}

SystemEditor shall open on the front most screen if it's a PublicScreen
else SystemEditor will open on the default PublicScreen.
If this also fails SystemEditor will open on the workbench screen.

Example: FRONTMOST (it's a switch)



@{b}@{u}One example for 'JUMP', 'LOADFILE' and 'WINCLOSEQUIT'@{ub}@{uu}

We want to jump directly into Node 2 -> Serial/Modem/Screen window.
On closing the Serial/Modem/Screen window the SystemEditor shall end:

1.Shell:> SystemEditor JUMP=5 WINCLOSEQUIT LOADFILE=2


@{b}@{u}Note@{ub}@{uu}

Arguments typed on starting the SystemEditor from CLI/Shell have a higher
priority than the ToolTypes. This is the reason for 'CHECK':- use this if
the @{"ToolType NOCHECK" link "SysEdToolTypes"} is set, but you will force SystemEditor
to check for directories and files. It's just for checking if all
files and directories are available.
Do this if something doesn't work or you have updated FAME.

@endnode

