@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatBBSName" "BBS Name"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): BBS Name
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the name of your BBS.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatBBSOrigin" "BBS Origin"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): BBS Origin
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the origin of your BBS (Country...)

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatSysOpName" "SysOp Name"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): SysOp Name
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here your SysOp name used for your BBS.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatBBSLocationPath" "BBS Location Path"


                @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): BBS Location Path
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the BBS location Path, normally 'FAME:'.

Note: It's better you do not use 'BBS:'! Use 'FAME:' instead, because if
      you use non FAME-Doors they may destroy your user.data/user.keys
      files if they are trying to write into them.

      From the release date of FAME on the assign FAME: is a *MUST* assign
      so there is no reason to change this path, except when running two
      FAME boards on one computer!!!

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatUserDataKeyPath" "UserData/Key Path"


                @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): UserData/Key Path
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the path of the user data files, normally 'FAME:UserData'.
You can change it to another location of your choice to have better security
against bad tools which are trying to access directly the user datas.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatUserDataName" "UserData Name"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): UserData Name
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The file name of user data file, normally 'user.data'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatUserKeysName" "UserKeys Name"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): UserKeys Name
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The file name of user key file, normally 'user.keys'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatFileCryptPW" "File Crypt PW"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): File Crypt PW
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The global password of yours to crypt files like uploads and more.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatNewUserLevel" "NewUser Level"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): NewUser Level
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level of new users. Normally 0.This means FAME doesn't allow users
with level 0 to reach the menu, or the newuser conference. They only can
leave a new user entry, and after it they will be logged out.

Because of this, they will see nothing more of your BBS.

To let them into the new user conference, you have to set this level to 1
or higher.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatShowBulltxt" "Show Bull.txt"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Show Bull.txt
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Display the <BBSLocation:Bull<x>.txt> or not.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatBullMinNumLines" "Bull Min NumLines"


                @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Bull Min NumLines
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum lines of Bull.txt before a pause prompt.

Usefull for endless animations. Use alternatively a number in the file comment
of the textfile itself.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatMinBreakLevel" "Min Break Level"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Min Break Level
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum level a user must have to use ctrl-c on Bull.txt.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatUPWFailUEALLLvl" "UPWFail UEALLLvl"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): UPWFail UEALLLvl
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

On user password fail the level of UEALL messages to notify the pw failure
to them.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatFileDescUnderLine" "FileDescUnderLine"


                @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): FileDescUnderLine
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The borderline for filelistings.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatMaxFidLines" "Max Fid Lines"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Max Fid Lines
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The maximum of lines a file identify descrition (file_id.diz) must have.

Default: 12

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatDefNumLines" "Def NumLines"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Def NumLines
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Default number of lines on text files if no number of lines can be found.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatNumberofNodes" "Number of Nodes"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Number of Nodes
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The number of nodes you have.

Note: SystemEditor updates this entry itself.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatUserlimit" "Userlimit"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Userlimit
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The limit of users in your BBS. If this value is reached, FAME wont let
new user get a new user entry.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatMaxNameFailure" "Max Name Failure"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Max Name Failure
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The number of false name entries before FAME drops the carrier.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatMaxUserPWFailure" "Max UserPW Failure"


                @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Max UserPW Failure
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The number of user password fails before FAME drops the carrier.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatMaxSysPWFailure" "Max SysPW Failure"


                @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Max SysPW Failure
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The number of system password fails before FAME drops carrier.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatMaxNUPFailure" "Max NUP Failure"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Max NUP Failure
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The number of new user password fails before FAME drops the carrier.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatMaxUserHacks" "Max User Hacks"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Max User Hacks
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}
The number of user hacks (wrong user passwords) on a account before
FAME inactivates this account.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatDoonMaxUserHacks" "Do on Max User Hacks"


               @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Do on Max User Hacks
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

What FAME does if 'Max User Hacks' is reached on an account:

-Nothing                : Do nothing.
-UserKick/Notify SysOp  : Drop carrier and write a mail to the sysop.
-UserKick/Notify SysOp's: Drop carrier and writes UEALL's to SysOp and
                          CoSysOp's (Level 250).
-Start Capture          : Start a capture on this user to watch the activities 
                          when the user gets into the BBS next time.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatEmergencyPW" "EmergencyPW"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): EmergencyPW
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The password for emergency menu command.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatFileNumbers" "FileNumbers"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): FileNumbers
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Show file numbers on file listings.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatDateandBytes" "Date and Bytes"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Date and Bytes
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Show date and bytes on file listings.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatAllowUserFileBase" "Allow UserFileBase"


                @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Allow UserFileBase
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable UserFileBase global for FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESysDatDoFileDescripts" "Do File Descripts"


                @{b}SystemEditor (System Datas): Do File Descripts
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Show file descriptions on file listings.

@endnode

