@node "SENodeNodeStartPath" "Node Start Path"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (Node Edit): Node Start Path
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The location and name of @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"}, normally '<BBSLocation>:Modules/MainPart'.
If you have @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"} resident loaded and want to use @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"} resident,
you musn't write the path here! Write only the resident name like 'MainPart'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SENodeNodePriority" "Node Priority"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Node Edit): Node Priority
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The priority of this Node.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SENodeScreensPath" "Screens Path"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Node Edit): Screens Path
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The path for the most text files needed by FAME.
Normally located in '<BBSLocation>:Screens/Node<x>'.

If you want to have the same text files for all Nodes, it's easier to use
the same path for all Nodes, like: '<BBSLocation>:Screens'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SENodeFilesnotAllowP" "Filesnot Allow. P."


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Node Edit): Filesnot Allow. P.
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Files not allowed to be uploaded can be located in a special directory,
normally '<BBSLocation>:FilesNot'.

They can have 0 bytes of file size.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SENodeLogoffBatch" "Logoff Batch"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Node Edit): Logoff Batch
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

It's not the best way to have loggoff tools, like bulletins,and other tools, in the
same batch file, but you can have this. For this just write your normal
AmigaOs batch and inform FAME here about it's location.

Normally '<BBSLocation>:Node<x>/Logoff.bat'.

Note: There is a better way for bulletins and stuff,
      just read the chapter @{" Batches " link "Batches" 0}.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

