@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeINamesNotAllowed" "NamesNotAllowed"


                @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): NamesNotAllowed
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here where the file 'NamesNotAllowed.txt' can be found.
Normally '<BBSLocation>:NamesNotAllowed.txt'.

Note: Place into this text file under the following names: - SYSOP
                                                           - ALL
                                                           - EALL
                                                           - UEALL
                                                           - <NewUserKey>

...and others like 'fuck' etc etc ...

These names cannot be used as usernames.

The four top names are reserved for FAME. For <NewUserKey> see the
Title under @{"NewUserKey" link "SEMNodeINewUserKey"}.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeINETNodeID" "NET NodeID"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): NET NodeID
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The id if you are running a network.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeINewUserKey" "NewUserKey"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): NewUserKey
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the new user key.

Note: Define the same name here as in the text file NamesNotAllowed.txt
      see: @{"NamesNotAllowed" link "SEMNodeINamesNotAllowed"}.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIRipSuffixdefine" "RipSuffix define"


                @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): RipSuffix define
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the suffix of RIP files.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeI1Timeout" "1. Timeout"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): 1. Timeout
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the first timeout. On first timeout the Node sends a beep and
starts the second timeout.

Default: 180 seconds.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeI2Timeout" "2. Timeout"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): 2. Timeout
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the second timeout. If also the second timeout is reached,
the user will be kicked off, and the Node resets for the next caller.

Default: 60 seconds.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIDoorTimeOut" "DoorTimeOut"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): DoorTimeOut
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the timout a door can have until nothing happens.

Default 120 seconds.

Note: It's dependant on the door to react correctly on doorport results to
      quit immediatly.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIBaudRate" "BaudRate"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): BaudRate
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here a specific baud rate, watched by the Node on connecting, to check
if the SysOp is willing to allow such a connect between @{"StartTime" link "SEMNodeIStartTime"} and @{"EndTime" link "SEMNodeIEndTime"}.

If the baud rate you type in here is already available it will be loaded and
the gadgets @{"StartTime" link "SEMNodeIStartTime"} and @{"EndTime" link "SEMNodeIEndTime"} will be filled.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIStartTime" "StartTime"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): StartTime
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The start time for connects with the  @{"BaudRate" link "SEMNodeIBaudRate"} defined rate.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIEndTime" "EndTime"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): EndTime
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The end time for connects with the  @{"BaudRate" link "SEMNodeIBaudRate"} defined rate.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeISAVE" "SAVE"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): SAVE
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

To save the current visable contends of the gadgets:

@{"BaudRate" link "SEMNodeIBaudRate"}, @{"StartTime" link "SEMNodeIStartTime"} and @{"EndTime"
under the name @{"BaudRate" link "SEMNodeIBaudRate"}.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIDELETE" "DELETE"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): DELETE
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

To delete the current @{"BaudRate" link "SEMNodeIBaudRate"}.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIIfBaudTimenotfound" "If BaudTime not found"


             @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): If BaudTime not found
            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

What to do if the connect @{"BaudRate" link "SEMNodeIBaudRate"} is not defined on a user logon:

 -Use 24 hours  : Let those users 24 hours a day connecting to this Node.
 -Don't let in! : Don't let undefined connects into this Node.
 -Use lower one : Look for the next lower one defined @{"BaudRate" link "SEMNodeIBaudRate"} and use
                  those defined times.
 -Use higher one: Look for the next higher one defined @{"BaudRate" link "SEMNodeIBaudRate"} and use
                  those defined times.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIDisplayPasswordstoSysOp" "Display Passwords to SysOp"


           @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Display Passwords to SysOp
          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Display all passwords a user enters on SysOp's console.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIInternalUserEd" "Internal UserEd"


                @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Internal UserEd
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

What to do if the internal usered is used while a user is online:

-Hidden to User: Stop the serial in/output to the user until the sysop
                 has finished using it.
-Inform User   : Inform the user about it and then do the same as Hidden to User.
-Show to User  : Stop the serial input, but the user can see what the
                 SysOp does.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeINewUser" "NewUser"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): NewUser
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

What to do if someone enters a non-used user name:

-No NewUser     : No new users allowed, drop him.
-NewUser Ask    : Start at the beginning as a newuser.
-NewUserKey Wait: The same as No NewUser, but indirectly. If the user knows
                  the NewUserKey, defined above, and he enters it as a
                  user name in the Username Prompt correctly he will continue
                  as a new user.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIMinUsNaChars" "MinUsNaChars"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): MinUsNaChars
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define the minimum chars for user names on user name prompts
(login, change user name and new user entry).

Default: 3.

See also: @{"MinUsPWChars" link "SEMNodeIMinUsPWChars"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIMinUsPWChars" "MinUsPWChars"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): MinUsPWChars
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define the minimum chars for user passwords on user password prompts
(change password and new user entry).

Default: 3.

See also: @{"MinUsNaChars" link "SEMNodeIMinUsNaChars"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIRipCON" "Rip CON"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Rip CON
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

What to do on console if someone uses RIP graphics:

-View Norm. Text: View the normal text file instead.
-Do Nothing     : Do nothing.
-Note on CON    : Inform the SysOp that this RIP file will be displayed to
                  the user.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIConfPreset" "Conf. Preset"


               @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Conference Preset
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

What to do if you set a preset in the internal user editor:

- Ask for Preset: Internal user editor asks for "Preset on all Confs".
- No Preset     : Internal user editor don't asks for "Preset on all Confs".
- Auto Preset   : Internal user editor sets the preset to all confs.

@endnode

