@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIAsyncStartbatches" "Async. Startbatches"


              @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Async. Startbatches
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If checked, Startbatches will be started asynchronously.

Note: Only tools which are marked as async. maybe in their doc files,
      should be started in this way.

      This here is the global flag I.E what to do if no filecomment is found.

      Every batch file can have a filecommend which marks the batch as
      async or not.

      The filecommends must be: 'ASYNCHRON' or 'SYNCHRON'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIAsyncLogonbatches" "Async. Logonbatches"


              @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Async. Logonbatches
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If checked Logonbatches will be started asynchronously

Note: Only tools which are marked as async. maybe in their doc files,
      should be started in this way.

      This here is the global flag,I.E. what to  do if no filecomment is found.

      Every batch file can have a filecommend which marked the batch as
      async or not.

      The filecommends must be: 'ASYNCHRON' or 'SYNCHRON'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIAsyncLogoffbatches" "Async. Logoffbatches"


              @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Async. Logoffbatches
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If checked Logoffbatches will be started asynchronously

Note: Only tools which are marked as async. maybe in their doc files,
      should be started in this way.

      This here is the global flag, I.E.what to do if no filecomment is found.

      Every batch file can have a filecommend which marked the batch as
      async or not.

      The filecommends must be: 'ASYNCHRON' or 'SYNCHRON'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIAsyncShutDownbatches" "Async. ShutDownbatches"


             @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Async. ShutDownbatches
            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If checked ShutDownbatches will be started asynchronously.

Note: Only tools which are marked as async. maybe in their doc files,
      should be started in this way.

      This here is the global flag,I.E. what to do if no filecomment is found.

      Every batch file can have a filecommend which marked the batch as
      async or not.

      The filecommends must be: 'ASYNCHRON' or 'SYNCHRON'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIDisplayzerobytes" "Display zero bytes"


               @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Display zero bytes
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If not checked, the result values of a user, for example upload bytes/files
available, will be displayed correctly, else if checked all negativ values
will be displayed as 0.

Example: A user has 10 uploads, 20 downloads and a ratio of 1:1.
         The result is -10 files available and will be displayed to the user
         as -10, but if this checkmark is on the Node will display 0.
         Usable for user which have a disabled to download as much as they
         are willing to. But i think it's good to show such a user his negativ
         bytes... now he can see what he has to upload if he 
         lost his disabled ratio. To do it like this you must leave this unchecked.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIShanghaiWindows" "Shanghai Windows"


                @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Shanghai Windows
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Use shanghai windows.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIRelativeConferences" "Relative Conferences"


              @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): Relative Conferences
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Hide conferences to a user on which a user has no access.
If relative conferences is on the conferences will be newly sorted depending
on users conference access.

Example:

Relative Conferences off:

1 X Access to this conference
2 - No access to this conference
3 X Access to this conference
4 - No access to this conference
5 X Access to this conference

Relative Conferences on:

1 X Access to this conference
2 X Access to this conference
3 X Access to this conference

The new 1 is the old 1,
the new 2 is the old 3 and
the new 3 is the old 5.

As you can see the conferences will be new sorted for the user and confs
between are no longer visable.

Note: Internal FAME handles all real not relative, for door coders, FAMEDoorPort
      has enough ability to handle the conferences.

      This means that for the user, he joins into conf 3 if he types "J 3"
      but internal FAME jumps in the real conf nr. 5.

      If a door requests the current conference number it will also get the
      conf nr. 5 and not 3.

      A door must check if relative conferences is on: a command exists for
      this. If the door must load/save something directly into the conference,
      It always must use the REAL number!

      On relative, only the visible numbers are other numbers, but not in real.

      The doorport also is able to convert numbers between relative and real
      conference numbers.

@endnode

