Note: This value will normally be set automatically if you select a
      screenmode.
      It's not possible to type invalid or out of range values in here else
      the SystemEditor will set it back to a default value.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScScrTopEdge" "ScrTopEdge"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): ScrTopEdge
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Top edge of the Node screen.

Note: This value will normally be set automatically if you select a
      screenmode.
      It's not possible to type invalid or out of range values in here else
      the SystemEditor will set it back to a default value.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScScrWidth" "ScrWidth"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): ScrWidth
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Screen width.

Note: This value will normally be set automatically if you select a
      screenmode.
      It's not possible to type invalid or out of range values in here else
      the SystemEditor will set it back to a default value.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScScrHight" "ScrHight"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): ScrHight
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Screen hight.

Note: This value will normally be set automatically if you select a
      screenmode.
      It's not possible to type invalid or out of range values in here else
      the SystemEditor will set it back to a default value.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScWndLeftEdge" "WndLeftEdge"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): WndLeftEdge
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Left edge of the Node backdrop window.

Note: This value will normally be set automatically if you select a
      screenmode.
      It's not possible to type invalid or out of range values in here else
      the SystemEditor will set it back to a default value.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScWndTopEdge" "WndTopEdge"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): WndTopEdge
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Top edge of the Node backdrop window.

Note: This value will normally be set automatically if you select a
      screenmode.
      It's not possible to type invalid or out of range values in here else
      the SystemEditor will set it back to a default value.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScWndWidth" "WndWidth"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): WndWidth
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Node backdrop window width.

Note: This value will normally be set automatically if you select a
      screenmode.
      It's not possible to type invalid or out of range values in here else
      the SystemEditor will set it back to a default value.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScWndHight" "WndHight"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): WndHight
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Node backdrop window hight.

Note: This value will normally be set automatically if you select a
      screenmode including the normal window offsets.

      Change the WndHight to a smaller one if you want to reserve a part of
      the publicscreen for usage with a shell/editor if you are a coder.

      It's not possible to type invalid or out of range values in here else
      the SystemEditor will set it back to a default value.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScScreenMode" "Screen Mode"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Screen Mode
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If you have AmigaOS 3.x and higher you can pop up a ScreenModeRequester
to select the ScreenMode. You also can switch the AutoScrollFlag off if you
open the ScreenModeRequester. If you have AmigaOS 2.x you can't use this
popupgadget and the ScreenModeRequester.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScOS2xOnly" "OS 2.x Only"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): OS 2.x Only
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If you own AmigaOS 2.x you can select between six different ScreenModes:

-PAL HighRes
-PAL Highres Interlaced
-NTSC HighRes
-NTSC HighRes Interlaced
-Multiscan Productivity
-Euro:72Hz Productivity

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScFont" "Font"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Font
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The actual font name selected.
The popupgadget is used to select another font with the FontRequester.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScSize" "Size"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Size
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The actual font size selected.
The popupgadget is used to select another font size with the FontRequester.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScIconified" "Iconified"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Iconified
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Tells the Node that it starts iconified, what means the screen doesn't
appears.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScScrtoFront" "Scr to Front"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Scr to Front
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Tells the Node that you want the Node screen to pop up automatically on
starting the Node.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScBitPlanes" "BitPlanes"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): BitPlanes
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The number of bitplanes you want to use for the screen.

Bitplanes are:

 - 1 =   2 colors.
 - 2 =   4 colors.
 - 3 =   8 colors.
 - 4 =  16 colors.
 - 5 =  32 colors.
 - 6 =  64 colors.
 - 7 = 128 colors.
 - 8 = 256 colors.
 - ...

Note: If you can use the ScreenModeRequester you can select the number
      of colors  you want, and this will be entered in the BitPlanes gadget
      automatically as bitplanes.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScRADBoogie" "RADBoogie"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): RADBoogie
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable Serial high-speed mode.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScXDisabled" "XDisabled"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): XDisabled
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Disable XON/OFF.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoSc7Wire" "7Wire"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): 7Wire
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Seven-wire handshaking for RS-232-C communications.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScShared" "Shared"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Shared
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If enabled other tasks are allowed to use the same device and unit at the
same time as the Node.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScPalettePens" "Palette/Pens"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Palette/Pens
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

A Node emulation screen to configure screen settings and more directly.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScUseOwnDevUnit" "Use OwnDevUnit"


               @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Use OwnDevUnit
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable OwnDevUnit.library for easy device sharing with other tasks.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScNotuseifShared" "Not use if Shared"


             @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Not use if Shared
            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Do not use OwnDevUnit.library if serial device is @{"shared" link "SESeMoScShared"} open.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScReleaseOnline" "Release Online"


               @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Release Online
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Release the device also if a user is online and a task requests the device.

Note: This will drop the carrier on the users Node.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScDeviceReleaseKeepOpen" "Release/Keep Open"


             @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Release/Keep Open
            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Release the device or keep it open @{"(shared)" link "SESeMoScShared"} if another task requests our
device.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScBACK" "BACK"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): BACK
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Go back to previous window: Node Edit.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScSAVE" "SAVE"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): SAVE
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Save the current settings depending to the actual Node.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScSAVEUSE" "SAVE+USE"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): SAVE+USE
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Save the current settings depending to the actual Node.

If FAME is running it will activate the new changes.

                            @{fg shine}NOT IMPLEMENTED YET !!!@{fg text}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScUSE" "USE"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): USE
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If FAME is running it will activate the  new changes.

                            @{fg shine}NOT IMPLEMENTED YET !!!@{fg text}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Conferences" "Conferences"


                           @{b}SystemEditor: Conferences
                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}


@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure all conference dependant options.
What you configure here is local and only available for the current conf.

                @{"   Conference Name    " link "SEConfConferenceName"} @{"  Priority MSG Level  " link "SEConfPriorityMSGLevel"}
                @{" Conference Location  " link "SEConfConferenceLocation"} @{"    Number of Dirs    " link "SEConfNumberofDirs"}
                @{"    Upload Path I     " link "SEConfUploadPathI"} @{" Bull.txt Min NumLine " link "SEConfBulltxtMinNumLine"}
                @{"   Download Path I    " link "SEConfDownloadPathI"} @{"       Min Brk        " link "SEConfMinBrkBull"}
                @{"  Additio. Ul Paths   " link "SEConfAdditioUlPaths"} @{" Menu.txt Min NumLine " link "SEConfMenutxtMinNumLine"}
                @{"  Additio. Dl Paths   " link "SEConfAdditioDlPaths"} @{"       Min Brk        " link "SEConfMinBrkMenu"}
                @{"  Free Upload Level   " link "SEConfFreeUploadLevel"} @{" FileHelp Min NumLine " link "SEConfFileHelpMinNumLine"}
                @{" Free Download Level  " link "SEConfFreeDownloadLevel"} @{"       Min Brk        " link "SEConfMinBrkFileHelp"}
                @{"   Read Msg. Level    " link "SEConfReadMsgLevel"} @{" DownMsg Min NumLines " link "SEConfDownMsgMinNumLines"}
                @{"   Write Msg. Level   " link "SEConfWriteMsgLevel"} @{"       Min Brk        " link "SEConfMinBrkDownMsg"}
                @{"     Upload Level     " link "SEConfUploadLevel"} @{"  UpMsg Min NumLines  " link "SEConfUpMsgMinNumLines"}
                @{"    Download Level    " link "SEConfDownloadLevel"} @{"       Min Brk        " link "SEConfMinBrkUpMsg"}
                @{"   Filelst View Lvl   " link "SEConfFilelstViewLvl"} @{"     SentBy Files     " link "SEConfSentByFiles"}
                @{"  Private MSG Level   " link "SEConfPrivateMSGLevel"} @{"  User SentBy Files   " link "SEConfUserSentByFiles"}
                @{"   Public MSG Level   " link "SEConfPublicMSGLevel"} @{"   Give Ul Bytes *    " link "SEConfGiveUlBytes"}
                @{"   UEALL MSG Level    " link "SEConfUEALLMSGLevel"} @{"   Give Dl Bytes *    " link "SEConfGiveDlBytes"}
                @{"  1.UlPath Behind A.  " link "SEConfFUlPathBehindA"} @{"   AmigaDOS File Len  " link "SEConfAmigaDOSFileLen"}

                @{"  Actual Conference   " link "SEConfActualConference"} @{"         GET          " link "SEConfGET"}
                @{"        SELECT        " link "SEConfSELECT"} @{"       DEFAULT        " link "SEConfDEFAULT"}
                @{"          <           " link "SEConfLeft"} @{"        DELETE        " link "SEConfDELETE"}
                @{"          >           " link "SEConfRight"} @{"         BACK         " link "SEConfBACK"}
                @{"      Available       " link "SEConfAvailable"} @{"         SAVE         " link "SEConfSAVE"}
                @{"        CLONE         " link "SEConfCLONE"} @{"       SAVE+USE       " link "SEConfSAVEUSE"}
                @{"         COPY         " link "SEConfCOPY"} @{"         USE          " link "SEConfUSE"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfConferenceName" "Conference Name"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Conference Name
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the name of the conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfConferenceLocation" "Conference Location"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Conference Location
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

This must be the location path of the conference,
for example: '<BBSLocation>:Conferences/MyConf'

Note: This gadget and it's following four path gadgets will be filled
      automatically if you select with Conference Location's pop up gadget
      path.
      Use the Filerequester to create a new path for the conference.
      If you have done this and you click on ok gadget in the Filerequester
      this selected path will be inserted into the other four gadgets too,
      but only if there are no other chars typed in, they must be empty or
      >       „ !Change Me! „... must be in this gadget here.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfUploadPathI" "Upload Path I"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Upload Path I
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The normal (first) upload path for uploads.

Note: If you have the SystemEditor let you specify the first 5 gadgets,
      see: @{"Conference Location" link "SEConfConferenceLocation"}, the appendix Upload/
      is automatically added, you may let it in this case:- the non existant
      path 'upload' will be created if you save the conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfDownloadPathI" "Download Path I"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Download Path I
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The normal (first) download path for downloads.

Note: If you have the SystemEditor let you specify the first 5 gadgets,
      see: @{"Conference Location" link "SEConfConferenceLocation"}, the appendix Download/
      is automatically added, you may let it in this case:- the not existing
      path 'Download' will be created if you save the conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfAdditioUlPaths" "Additio. Ul Paths"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Additional Ul Paths
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Here you can set the location of a text file which
can hold additional upload paths like:

here:
there:stuff/
...

Normally: '<BBSLocation>:Conferences/MyConf/AddUlPaths.txt'

Note: If you have the SystemEditor let you specify the first 5 gadgets,
      see: @{"Conference Location" link "SEConfConferenceLocation"}, the appendix AddUlPaths.txt
      is automatically added, you may let it in this case, the not existing
      file AddUlPaths.txt will be created if you save the conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfAdditioDlPaths" "Additio. Dl Paths"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Additional Dl Paths
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Here you can set the location of a text file which
can hold additional download paths like:

here:
there:stuff/
...

Normally: '<BBSLocation>:Conferences/MyConf/AddDlPaths.txt'

Note: If you have the SystemEditor let you specify the first 5 gadgets,
      see: @{"Conference Location" link "SEConfConferenceLocation"}, the appendix AddDlPaths.txt
      is automatically added, you may let it in this case, the not existing
      file AddDlPaths.txt will be created if you save the conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfFreeUploadLevel" "Free Upload Level"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Free Upload Level
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which all uploads give no credits.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfFreeDownloadLevel" "Free Download Level"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Free Download Level
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which on downloads give no credits.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfReadMsgLevel" "Read Msg. Level"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Read Msg. Level
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which messages can be read.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfWriteMsgLevel" "Write Msg. Level"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Write Msg. Level
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which messages can be written.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfUploadLevel" "Upload Level"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Upload Level
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which uploading is allowed here.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfDownloadLevel" "Download Level"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Download Level
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which downloading is allowed here.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfFilelstViewLvl" "Filelst View Lvl"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Filelst View Lvl
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which file list reading is allowed here.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfPrivateMSGLevel" "Private MSG Level"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Private MSG Level
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which private message writing is allowed here.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfPublicMSGLevel" "Public MSG Level"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Public MSG Level
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which public message writing is allowed here.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfUEALLMSGLevel" "UEALL MSG Level"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): UEALL MSG Level
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which UEALL message reading/writing is allowed here.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfPriorityMSGLevel" "Priority MSG Level"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Priority MSG Level
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level from which priority message writing is allowed here.

You can also specify with the next right gadget if this level is the minimum
or maximum or you can switch it completely off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfNumberofDirs" "Number of Dirs"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Number of Dirs
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The number of Upload directories. Normally 2, the first is a type of hold
file for users, to check for older deleted files. The last here is 2:- it
is the file where all new uploads will be inserted in. If you have more than
2 directories the last one will be the one.

If this value is zero ('0') the node will tell the user:
'There are no files in this conference.'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfBulltxtMinNumLine" "Bull.txt Min NumLine"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Bull.txt Min NumLine
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum no of lines in Bull.txt before pause prompt.

Useful for long animations. Use alternatively a number in the file comment
of the textfile itself.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfMinBrkBull" "Min Brk Bull.txt"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Min Brk Bull.txt
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum level a user must have to use ctrl-c on Bull.txt.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfMenutxtMinNumLine" "Menu.txt Min NumLine"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Menu.txt Min NumLine
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum no of lines in Menu.txt before pause prompt.

Usefull for long animations. Use alternatively a number in the file comment
of the textfile itself.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfMinBrkMenu" "Min Brk Menu.txt"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Min Brk Menu.txt
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum level a user must have to use ctrl-c on Menu.txt.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfFileHelpMinNumLine" "FileHelp.txt Min NumLine"


              @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): FileHelp.txt Min NumLine
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum no of lines in FileHelp.txt before pause prompt.

Useful for long animations. Use alternatively a number in the file comment
of the textfile itself.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfMinBrkFileHelp" "Min Brk FileHelp.txt"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Min Brk FileHelp.txt
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum level a user must have to use ctrl-c on FileHelp.txt.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfDownMsgMinNumLines" "DownloadMsg.txt Min NumLines"


            @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): DownloadMsg.txt Min NumLines
           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum no of lines in Downloadmsg.txt before pause prompt.

Useful for long animations. Use alternatively a number in the file comment
of the textfile itself.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfMinBrkDownMsg" "Min Brk DownloadMsg.txt"


              @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Min Brk DownloadMsg.txt
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum level a user must have to use ctrl-c on Downloadmsg.txt.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfUpMsgMinNumLines" "UploadMsg.txt Min NumLines"


             @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): UploadMsg.txt Min NumLines
            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum no of lines in Uploadmsg.txt before pause prompt.

Usefull for long animations. Use alternatively a number in the file comment
of the textfile itself.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfMinBrkUpMsg" "Min Brk UploadMsg.txt"


               @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Min Brk UploadMsg.txt
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The minimum level a user must have to use ctrl-c on Uploadmsg.txt.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfSentByFiles" "SentBy Files"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): SentBy Files
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Checked if you want to have taglines for every upload in file lists.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfUserSentByFiles" "User SentBy Files"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): User SentBy Files
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Checked if you want that users can enter and edit their own taglines
for SentBy.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfGiveUlBytes" "Give Ul Bytes *"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Give Ul Bytes *
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

How many Bytes FAME should give additional to the user ratio for uploads.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfGiveDlBytes" "Give Dl Bytes *"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Give Dl Bytes *
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

How many Bytes FAME should give additional to the user ratio for downloads.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfFUlPathBehindA" "1.UlPath Behind A."

                               @{b}1.UlPath Behind A.
                              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

First upload path behind additional upload paths means on using the first
and additional upload pathes for sorting in uploaded files @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"} will
first use the additional ones and then the first. This means in this case
the first upload path will be the last one and a kind of empty buffer if
all other pathes are full.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfAmigaDOSFileLen" "AmigaDOS File Len"

                               @{b}AmigaDOS File Len
                              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If set files where file names are up to 30 chars can be uploaded into this
conference, if not file names can only be 12 chars long.

File names with 30 chars in length are AmigaDOS file name length compatible.
File names with 12 chars in length are PC file name length compatible.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfActualConference" "Actual Conference"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Actual Conference
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the number of an available conference or the next one after the
highest conference available to load the conference settings or create a new
conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfSELECT" "SELECT"


                      @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): SELECT
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

This one will pop up a number selector window for easy usage to select
a conference number of an available conference or the next one after the
highest conference available to load the conference settings or create a
new conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfLeft" "<"


                         @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): <
                        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Select the previous conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfRight" ">"


                         @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): >
                        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Select the next conference or create a new one if you were already at the
last available conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfAvailable" "Available"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Available
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

To select an available conference, no new conference creation possible.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfCLONE" "CLONE"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): CLONE
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Clone the current selected conference to a new one which will be then the
last conference available. The new one will be equal with it's settings to
the conference which has been cloned.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfCOPY" "COPY"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): COPY
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Copy the contends of the current conference into a conference which already
exists.

This one will overwrite the settings of the conference which will be used to
copy the current conference contents into.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfGET" "GET"


                        @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): GET
                       ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Get the settings of a already existing conference into the currently
selected conference.

This one will overwrite the settings of the current selected conference.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfDEFAULT" "DEFAULT"


                      @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): DEFAULT
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Set the conference settings to a default value.

This one will overwrite the settings of the current selected conference.

@endnode

