                              @{" Conference Access " link "ConferenceAccess" 0}
                              @{"     Presets       " link "Presets" 0}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Levels" "Levels"


                             @{b}SystemEditor: Levels
                            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure all level dependant options.
The options configured for a level will be used to define what a user is
able to do in the bbs and what not.

If a user comes into the bbs and no level configfile exists for the user
the next lower one will be used.

On a user logon the node first tries to find a level with the user number
which will look like: "FAME:Settings/Access/Levels/<usernumber>.dat".
If this is not found the node tries to find a level with the user name
which will look like: "FAME:Settings/Access/Levels/<username>.dat".
If this also can't be found the node tries to find a level with the users
level which will look like:
"FAME:Settings/Access/Levels/Level<userlevel>.dat". 
If this also can't be find the node tries to load the next lower one.
If nothing can be found the node will set limited default values.

