@REM==============================================================================

@node "FileCheckers" "File Checkers"


                         @{b}SystemEditor: File Checkers
                        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure filecheckers.

Filecheckers are needed to check the uploaded files for errors.

                          @{"        Checker         " link "SEFileChkChecker"}
                          @{"    Extension (.#?)     " link "SEFileChkExtension"}
                          @{" Other Extension (.#?)  " link "SEFileChkOtherExt"}
                          @{"          NEW           " link "SEFileChkNEW"}
                          @{"      Checker Path      " link "SEFileChkCheckerPath"}
                          @{"       Stack Size       " link "SEFileChkStackSize"}
                          @{"        Priority        " link "SEFileChkPriority"}
                          @{"        Options         " link "SEFileChkOptions"}
                          @{"      Error 1 - 5       " link "SEFileChkError1to5"}
                          @{"    FileId Extractor    " link "SEFileChkFileId Extractor"}
                          @{"    FidEx Stack Size    " link "SEFileChkFidExStackSize"}

                          @{"          SAVE          " link "SEFileChkSAVE"}
                          @{"          BACK          " link "SEFileChkBACK"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkChecker" "Checker"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Checker
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable the current checker.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkExtension" "Extension (.#?)"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Extension (.#?)
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Select between different known filetypes (checkers).

Note: Select or Cycle! means select via file-requester a filetype (checker)
      from disk or cycle with this gadget to a known checker.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkOtherExt" "Other Extension (.#?)"


              @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Other Extension (.#?)
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Use the popup gadget to select a filetype/checker/extension via
file-requester.

The string gadget is only usable if you have klicked on @{"NEW" link "SEFileChkNEW"} to generate a
new filetype/checker/extension.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkNEW" "NEW"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): NEW
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Generate a completely new filetype/checker/extension.
If you use this gadget the gadget @{"Other Extension (.#?)" link "SEFileChkOtherExt"} will be usable.
Type here the extendion of the new filetype/checker.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkCheckerPath" "Checker Path"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Checker Path
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the full path to the filechecker which shall be used for the
current filetype/extension.

You can also use the popup gadget to select the filechecker via
file-requester.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkStackSize" "Stack Size"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Stack Size
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the stack size needed be the filechecker for the current
filetype/extension.

Note: See the documents of the filechecker you use for details.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkPriority" "Priority"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Priority
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the priority which shall be used by the filechecker for the
current filetype/extension.

Note: Default is -1, because most filecheckers will take too much CPU
      resources. On a higher priority it may interrupt your BBS.
      -1 is totally enough especially for background checking.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkOptions" "Options"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Options
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the options needed by the filechecker to test the file of the
current filetype/extension.

Note: See the documents of the filechecker you use for details.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkError1to5" "Error 1 - 5"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Error 1 - 5
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here up to 5 possible error message strings produced by the
filechecker, used for the current filetype/extension, if they find errors
in a file/archive.

Note: See the documents of the filechecker you use for details.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkFileId Extractor" "FileId Extractor"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): FileId Extractor
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the full path to the filechecker/packer/FileIdExtractor tool
you use to extract the file 'FILE_ID.DIZ' out of a file/archive.

Those tools will need options and the source file + the output path.
Use the keywords '%F' and '%W' (%F=From File %W=Work Path) to build the
needed options string you have to place after the full path to the
used tool.

Example for LHA: 'LHA -q e %F FILE_ID.DIZ %W'
Example for LZX: 'LZX -a x %F FILE_ID.DIZ %W'
Example for DMS: 'DMSDescript x %WFILE_ID.DIZ %F'
Example for EXE: 'EXEDescript x %WFILE_ID.DIZ %F'
Example for TXT: 'TXTEXTRACT e %WFILE_ID.DIZ %F'

Note: The file created must be located in the same Node as the uploaded
      file, but in the Work directory and must have the name 'FILE_ID.DIZ'.
      '%W' will be the path to the Work directory of the same Node.
      '%F' is the full path to the Playpen directory of the Node + filename.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkFidExStackSize" "FidEx Stack Size"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): FidEx Stack Size
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the stack size needed be the filechecker/packer/FileIdExtractor
tool for the current filetype/extension.

Note: See the documents of the tool you use for details.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkSAVE" "SAVE"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): SAVE
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Save the File Checkers settings.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkBACK" "BACK"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): BACK
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Cancel this window and go back into the main window of the SystemEditor.

@endnode

