@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModWriteHydLog" "Write (Hydra) Logfile"


              @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Write (Hydra) Logfile
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable log writings into file 'FAME:Node<x>/Hydra.Log'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModRemWndPos" "Remember Window positions"


            @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Remember Window positions
           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{"FAMEHydra" link "FAMEHydra.guide/Main"} will be able to remember every window position and size if you
change them while @{"FAMEHydra" link "FAMEHydra.guide/Main"} is running.

@{"FAMEHydra" link "FAMEHydra.guide/Main"} remembers the positions and sizes Node depended.

To get the origin positions and sizes back delete the file
'FAME:Settings/Node<x>/FAMEHydra.dat'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModDefPubScr" "Def. PublicScreen"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Def. PublicScreen
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

You can choose between four different public screen types:

 - FAME Node Public Screen   for the Node<x> screen.
 - SModem Public Screen      for SModem's own screen.
 - Workbench Public Screen   for the workbench screen.
 - FrontMost Public Screen   for the frontmost public screen.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModOtherPubScr" "Other PubScreen"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Other PubScreen
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Here you can define a completely from @{"Def. PublicScreen" link "SEExtXfrModDefPubScr"} different
public screen.

This will disable gadget @{"Def. PublicScreen" link "SEExtXfrModDefPubScr"}.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModFallBPubScr" "FallBack PubScreen"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): FallBack PubScreen
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Here you can define a fallback public screen.

This screen will be used if the screen defined with @{"Def. PublicScreen" link "SEExtXfrModDefPubScr"}
or @{"Other PubScreen" link "SEExtXfrModOtherPubScr"} is not available or can't be locked.

Note: If no screen is available or can't be locked including the fallback
      public screen, FAMESModem will try to lock your computers default
      public screen. If this failes too FAMESModem tries to lock the
      workbench.
      At the very last FAMESModem gives up and lets SModem open it's own
      screen.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModWriteSMdmLog" "Write (SModem) Logfile"


              @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Write (SModem) Logfile
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable log writings into file 'FAME:Node<x>/FAMESModem.Log'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModAutoExit" "Auto Exit"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Auto Exit
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Exit after transfer has completed.

@endnode

